               <head>Akbarnamah, daftar 1, part 1</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Akbarnāmah by Shaykh Abū al-Faẓl ibn Shaykh Mubārak Nāgawrī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80002413 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115921 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3919-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_5150639">Shaykh Abū al-Faẓl ibn Shaykh Mubārak Nāgawrī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_5150639" type="supplied">شيخ ابو الفضل ابن شيخ مبارك ناگورى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20880">Akbarnāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20880">اكبر نامه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Official regnal <term xml:lang="en">chronicle</term> for the reign of the Mughal Emperor  <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_3264079" role="subject">Akbar</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Comprises part 1 of the first <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">daftar</term> only
                        </p>
                        <p>
                           <term xml:lang="en">Rubrication</term> omitted throughout
                        </p>
                        <p>
                           <term xml:lang="en">Defective</term> at both ends, last 2 folios (ff. 276-7) modern replacements
                        </p>
                        <p>Folios disarranged, as many <term xml:lang="en">catchwords</term> have disappeared
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                        <p>Volume not identified as Akbarnāmah by W. Irvine, hence the inscription on a flyleaf, "History of the House of Timur. Presented for Mr W. Irvine by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7712" role="fmo">Moulvi Nur Mahomad</persName>, Amīr of Chunar, thro' <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="other">G. Jasper Nicholls</persName>. <name type="place">Benares</name> 12/3/92 "
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
